<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>A vehicle is travelling along a straight road at a constant velocity of <m>{16}</m> m/s. The driver observes a hazard and has a reaction time (thinking time) of <m>{0.7}</m> s before applying the brakes. Once the brakes are applied, the vehicle comes to a complete rest in <m>{5}</m> s.</p>

<ol>
    <li>Calculate the distance travelled during the thinking time (the period of constant velocity). <fillin characters="10" name="ans1"/>    m</li>
    <li>Determine the acceleration of the vehicle during the braking phase. <fillin characters="10" name="ans2"/> m/s²   </li>
    <li>Calculate the total displacement of the vehicle from the moment the hazard was seen until it came to a stop. <fillin characters="10" name="ans3"/> m   </li>
</ol>

<p><em>( Ensure you include the correct sign for acceleration.)</em></p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>1. Thinking Distance (Constant Velocity)</p>
<p>Since the velocity is constant during the reaction time, we use the standard speed-distance formula:</p>
<md>
<mrow>s_1 \amp = v \times t</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {16} \times {0.7}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {11.2} \text{ m}</mrow>
</md>

<p>2. Acceleration</p>
<p>Acceleration is the rate of change of velocity. Given that the final velocity <m>v</m> is 0:</p>
<md>
<mrow>a \amp = \frac{v - u}{t}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{0 - {16}}{{5}}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \mathbf{{-\frac{16}{5}} \text{ m/s}^2}</mrow>
</md>

<p>3. Total Displacement</p>
<p>The total displacement is the sum of the distance travelled while thinking and the distance travelled while braking:</p>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Total } s \amp = s_{\text{thinking}} + s_{\text{braking}}</mrow>
<mrow>s_{\text{braking}} \amp = ut + \frac{1}{2}at^2</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {16} \times {5} +\frac{1}{2} \times {-\frac{16}{5}} \times {5}^2</mrow>
<mrow>\text{Total } s \amp = {40.0} \text{ m}</mrow>
</md></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>11.2</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>-\frac{16}{5}</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>40.0</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>